This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on February 1, 2013. The memorandum is regarding the designation of officers of the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation to act as the Director of the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation in case the Director is unable to perform their duties. The memorandum establishes the order of succession for these officers to assume the role of Director. It also states exceptions and allows the President to depart from the memorandum in designating an acting Director. The memorandum supersedes a previous memorandum from December 9, 2008. It clarifies that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits and authorizes its publication in the Federal Register.